Set Up User Verification

User verification is available for a mobile app, an external website, or some Aura sites. It doesn't work with Experience Builder or Commerce Cloud sites.

To set up user verification:

1. Create a keyset by adding keys or an endpoint URL.
	* Click New Keyset and name it.
	* Choose whether to create from an endpoint URL or manually upload keys.
2. Turn on user verification in Setup:
	* From Quick Find, enter Messaging and select Messaging Settings.
	* Select the channel and click Edit.
	* Add User Verification checkbox.
3. Determine authorization token expiration time:
	* Control when a messaging session gets renewed by your website or mobile app.

Use the provided APIs to send the customer token to Salesforce:

Web
iOS
Android
